org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.impl

Class DefaultFeatureSelection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gvsig.tools.dispose.impl.AbstractDisposable
      • org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.impl.DefaultFeatureReferenceSelection
        • org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.impl.DefaultFeatureSelection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, DataSelection, DataSet, FeatureReferenceSelection, FeatureSelection, FeatureSet, Disposable, ComplexObservable, Observable, Observer, WeakReferencingObservable, Persistent, IndexedVisitable, Visitable

    public class DefaultFeatureSelection
extends DefaultFeatureReferenceSelection
implements FeatureSelection
    Default implementation of the FeatureSelection interface. Internally, only FeatureReference values are stored. This implementation performs better if used with the selection related methods: select, deselect and isSelected ones.

      • DefaultFeatureSelection

        public DefaultFeatureSelection()
        Constructor used by the persistence manager. Don't use directly. After to invoke this method, the persistence manager calls the the method loadFromState(PersistentState) to set the values of the internal attributes that this class needs to work.
